SUBSTITUTE FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 4824
A bill to amend 1998 PA 58, entitled
"Michigan liquor control code of 1998,"
by amending section 105 (MCL 436.1105), as amended by 2022 PA 226,
and by adding section 604.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 Sec. 105. (1) "Alcohol" means the product of distillation of
2 fermented liquid, whether or not rectified or diluted with water,
3 but does not mean ethyl or industrial alcohol, diluted or not, that
4 has been denatured or otherwise rendered unfit for beverage
5 purposes.
6 (2) "Alcohol vapor device" means any device that provides for
7 the use of air or oxygen bubbled through alcoholic liquor to
8 produce a vapor or mist that allows the user to inhale this
DAW H01013'25 (H-3) otqwb9

2
1 alcoholic vapor through the mouth or nose.
2 (3) "Alcoholic liquor" means any spirituous, vinous, malt, or
3 fermented liquor, powder, liquids, and compounds, whether or not
4 medicated, proprietary, or patented, and by whatever name called,
5 containing 1/2 of 1% or more of alcohol by volume that are fit for
6 use for food purposes or beverage purposes as defined and
7 classified by the commission according to alcoholic content as
8 belonging to 1 of the varieties defined in this chapter.
9 (4) "Alternating proprietorship" means 1 of the following:
10 (a) An arrangement in which 2 or more wine makers or small
11 wine makers take turns using the same space and equipment to
12 manufacture wine under section 603(9)(a) and in accordance with 27
13 CFR 24.136.
14 (b) An arrangement in which 2 or more brewers or micro brewers
15 take turns using the same space and equipment to manufacture beer
16 under section 603(9)(b) and in accordance with 27 CFR 25.52.
17 (5) "Approved tasting room" means a tasting room that is
18 approved by the commission. A licensee with an approved tasting
19 room is not a retail licensee as that term is used in this act and
20 the rules promulgated under this act except for sections 701, 801,
21 803, 815, 905, and 906.
22 (6) "Authorized distribution agent" means a person approved by
23 the commission to do 1 or more of the following:
24 (a) To store spirits owned by a supplier of spirits or the
25 commission.
26 (b) To deliver spirits sold by the commission to retail
27 licensees.
28 (c) To perform any function needed to store spirits owned by a
29 supplier of spirits or by the commission or to deliver spirits sold
DAW H01013'25 (H-3) otqwb9

3
1 by the commission to retail licensees.
2 (7) "Bar" means a barrier or counter at which alcoholic liquor
3 is sold to, served to, or consumed by customers.
4 (8) "Beer" means a beverage obtained by alcoholic fermentation
5 of an infusion or decoction of barley, malt, hops, sugar, or other
6 cereal in potable water.
7 (9) "Bottle" or "bottling" means a process, separate from
8 manufacturing, using owned or leased equipment to fill and seal a
9 container, including a keg, with alcoholic liquor for sale at
10 wholesale or retail in accordance with this act. Bottle or bottling
11 does not include filling a growler for sale at retail.
12 (10) "Brand" means any word, name, group of words, letter,
13 group of letters, symbol, trademark, group of symbols, or
14 combination thereof adopted and used by a supplier to name,
15 identify, or trademark a specific beer, malt beverage, wine, mixed
16 wine drink, or mixed spirit drink product. and to distinguish that
17 product from another beer, malt beverage, wine, mixed wine drink,
18 or mixed spirit drink product that is produced or marketed by that
19 or another supplier. As used in this subsection, "supplier" means a
20 brewer, micro brewer, an outstate seller of beer, a wine maker, a
21 small wine maker, an outstate seller of wine, a manufacturer of
22 mixed wine drink, an outstate seller of a mixed wine drink, a mixed
23 spirit drink manufacturer, or an outstate seller of mixed spirit
24 drink. A supplier's legal name, assumed name, or trade name, or any
25 doing-business-as name used by the supplier is considered a brand
26 name, identifier, or trademark if it is used in a manner that is
27 prominently featured on the container or packaging of the beer,
28 wine, mixed wine drink, or mixed spirit drink to market the product
29 and to identify the product, except under either of the following
DAW H01013'25 (H-3) otqwb9

4
1 circumstances:
2 (a) The use of the legal name, assumed name, trade name, or
3 doing-business-as name is not considered a brand name, identifier,
4 or trademark if it is not prominently featured on the container or
5 packaging of the beer, wine, mixed wine drink, or mixed spirit
6 drink.
7 (b) The use of the legal name, assumed name, trade name, or
8 doing-business-as name is not considered a brand name, identifier,
9 or trademark if it is used solely for any of the following
10 purposes:
11 (i) Identifying the supplier that manufactured the beer, wine,
12 mixed wine drink, or mixed spirit drink.
13 (ii) Identifying the supplier that has bottled the beer, wine,
14 mixed wine drink, or mixed spirit drink.
15 (iii) Identifying the supplier that has imported the beer, wine,
16 mixed wine drink, or mixed spirit drink.
17 (11) "Brand extension" means any brand that incorporates all
18 or a substantial part of the unique features of a preexisting
19 brand, regardless of whether the extension is beer, wine, mixed
20 wine drink, or mixed spirit drink.beer, wine, mixed wine drink, or
21 mixed spirit drink brand that is marketed, in any manner, using the
22 same name, identifier, or trademark associated with a brand that
23 has preceded it in being sold or offered for sale in this state, or
24 a derivative or portion of the name, identifier, or trademark and
25 that would lead a reasonable person to recognize its relationship
26 to an existing brand, regardless of any of the following:
27 (a) The addition of words or letters in a word.
28 (b) The addition of a name, identifier, or trademark.
29 (c) The addition of a symbol.
