5
1 (d) Any differences in the packaging, formulation, or
2 production of the beer, wine, mixed wine drink, or mixed spirit
3 drink or the shape, size, or type of container in which the beer,
4 wine, mixed wine drink, or mixed spirit drink is sold.
5 (e) Changes in the alcohol category used in the brand
6 extension. As used in this subdivision only, alcohol category means
7 a beer category, a wine category, a mixed wine drink category, or a
8 mixed spirit drink category.
9 (f) The manufacturer, importer, or licensed outstate seller of
10 the brand extension being different from the manufacturer,
11 importer, or licensed outstate seller of the underlying brand the
12 extension is based on.
13 (12) "Brandy" means an alcoholic liquor as defined in 27 CFR
14 5.22(d).5.145.
15 (13) "Brandy manufacturer" means a wine maker or a small wine
16 maker licensed under this act to manufacture brandy. A wine maker
17 or small wine maker authorized to manufacture brandy shall not
18 manufacture any other spirits. The commission may approve a brandy
19 manufacturer to sell brandy that it manufactures at retail in
20 accordance with section 537.
21 (14) "Brewer" means a person located in this state that is
22 licensed to manufacture beer and sell at retail in accordance with
23 section 537 and to licensed wholesalers beer manufactured by the
24 person.
25 (15) "Brewpub" means a license issued in conjunction with a
26 class C, tavern, class A hotel, or class B hotel license that
27 authorizes the person licensed with the class C, tavern, class A
28 hotel, or class B hotel license to manufacture and brew not more
29 than 18,000 barrels of beer per calendar year in this state and
