6
1 sell at its licensed premises the beer produced for consumption on
2 or off the licensed brewery premises in the manner provided for in
3 sections 405, 407, and 537.
4 (16) As used in subsection (10), "supplier" means a brewer, a
5 micro brewer, an outstate seller of beer, a wine maker, a small
6 wine maker, an outstate seller of wine, a manufacturer of a mixed
7 wine drink, an outstate seller of a mixed wine drink, a mixed
8 spirit drink manufacturer, and an outstate seller of a mixed spirit
9 drink.
10 (17) With regard to subsections (10) and (11), distribution
11 rights in effect as of the effective date of the amendatory act
12 that added this subsection are preserved. However, this subsection
13 does not limit application of subsection (11) to a beer, wine,
14 mixed wine drink, or mixed spirit drink that would be considered a
15 brand extension after the effective date of the amendatory act that
16 added this subsection that is based on a brand that was in
17 existence before the effective date of the amendatory act that
18 added this subsection.
19 Sec. 604. A supplier that registers a multibranded product
20 with the commission shall appoint the wholesaler or wholesalers
21 that have rights to the supplier's underlying brand. As used in
22 this section, "multibranded product" means any beer, wine, mixed
23 wine drink, or mixed spirit drink that includes 2 or more brands of
24 different suppliers.
25 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act does not take effect
26 unless House Bill No. 4823 of the 103rd Legislature is enacted into
27 law.
